# Admin Portal Navigation for Project Pages

When creating page stories under `src/stories/projects/`, always include the `AppNavigation` component from Circuit DS as the sidebar, wrapping the page content in a flex layout.

## Required Setup

Import and configure the navigation with the full admin portal menu items:

```typescript
import { markRaw } from 'vue';
import { AppNavigation } from '@jumpcloud/circuit/components';

// Heroicons
import {
  RocketLaunchIcon, HomeIcon, UserGroupIcon, ShieldCheckIcon,
  ChartBarSquareIcon, Cog6ToothIcon, BellIcon, UserIcon, UsersIcon,
  CommandLineIcon, ClipboardDocumentListIcon, ClipboardDocumentCheckIcon,
  ArrowRightStartOnRectangleIcon, ArrowTopRightOnSquareIcon,
} from '@heroicons/vue/24/outline';

// JumpCloud custom icons
import {
  DeviceManagementIcon, AccessIcon, DeviceListsIcon, DeviceGroupsIcon,
  SsoIcon, SaasManagementIcon, PasswordManagerIcon, WorkflowIcon,
} from '@jumpcloud/icons';
```

## Navigation Data

Use the reference story at `src/stories/circuit-ds/AdminPortalNavigation.stories.ts` for the complete `menuItems` and `profileMenuItems` arrays. Copy or import the data from there.

## Page Layout Pattern

Every project page must use this layout structure:

```html
<div class="flex h-screen overflow-hidden">
  <AppNavigation
    :menuItems="menuItems"
    :profileMenuItems="profileMenuItems"
    :activeItem="activeNavItem"
    :collapsible="true"
    :topNavToggle="true"
  />
  <div class="flex-1 flex flex-col min-w-0 overflow-auto">
    <!-- Page content here -->
  </div>
</div>
```

- Set `activeItem` to the lowercase label of the current page's nav section (e.g. `'device management'` for Device Management pages).
- Always use `layout: 'fullscreen'` in the story's `parameters`.
- Register `AppNavigation` in the `components` option of `defineComponent`.
